HEADWORD: Retroaction
<hw>Re`tro*ac"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧troaction</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Action returned,
or action backward.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Operation on something past or preceding.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Retroactive</ent>⟦br⟧
